body: @mfuntowicz currently we don't support this. we will try to add this support with the next onnxruntime release.

@MaajidKhan , just to quickly check if there are any updates on this topic? We are having the exact same issue here, for large NLP model, the ONNX export can only happen in `use_external_data_format` mode. But somehow ONNXRUNTIME can't load the model with external data..

Hi @yaxili96 . OpenVINO now has the functionality to support onnx models with Weights saved in external files.

**Reference:**
https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/openvino_docs_IE_DG_ONNX_Support.html#:~:text=Weights%20saved%20in%20external%20files%3A

so we should be able to expose this feature in OpenVINO Execution Provider for ONNXRuntime. Also, if you refer to above openvino documentation page, it has some catch.

> **Paths to external weight files are saved in an ONNX model; these paths are relative to the model's directory path. It means that if a model is located at: home/user/workspace/models/model.onnx and a file that contains external weights: home/user/workspace/models/data/weights.bin the path saved in model should be: data/weights.bin.**

So make sure when you are trying to Converting and Saving an ONNX Model to External Data, you adhere to the rule above.
You can use this onnx api to convert an ONNX model to external data.
https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/docs/ExternalData.md#converting-and-saving-an-onnx-model-to-external-data

**How can you test this feature out with onnxrt-openvino Execution Provider:**
Build OpenVINO Execution Provider for ONNXRuntime with the latest OpenVINO 2021.4 Version. Build onnxrt from Master.

Please comment out the following section of the code. (L51 to L57)
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/60c98a86b7f0deb2bbb9f9ca8ab5d14e2fc383e7/onnxruntime/core/providers/openvino/ov_versions/capability.cc#L51

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29036417/132123386-cd00cf3b-3569-4dc7-83cb-77ef0244a428.png)

Re-compile and then test out the feature and then let us know if this addresses your request. 

If the feature works, we will incorporate this change officially in our upcoming openvino Execution Provider release in october.

**PS:** I tried this with yolov4 model from onnx model zoo and with above changes, I was able to use openvino execution provider with an onnx model having external weights.

issue.title: [OpenVINO-EP] V3.2 Release

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: OpenVINO EP V3.2 Release with OpenVINO 2021.4.1 Version

**Motivation and Context**
- Added new features with this Release
- CL Cache Feature (supports VPU (Myriadx) and iGPU)
https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/openvino_docs_IE_DG_Model_caching_overview.html

**Note:** This feature is not yet available for the CPU plugin.

- Added build time option to disable subgraph partitioning for OpenVINO-EP. 
Meaning when this build option is used during build time, the graph will run on OV backend if the model is fully supported. If there is sub graph partitioning involved, the whole model will fully fallback to MLAS (default CPU EP)

- Added support for ONNX models with weights stored at external location
https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/openvino_docs_IE_DG_ONNX_Support.html (Refer to section **Weights saved in external files**)
**Addresses customer issue:**
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/6079

- Onnxruntime_perf_test Application can now infer model using Hetero and Multi options.

- Documentation PR.
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/9233
